        "text": "**For the sake of clarity**: the focus is not on \"scaling from below\". Spreading and applying the patterns of commoning to [Emulate & Federate] is certainly important, and it enacts what we call [[intercommoning]]. Nonetheless, it's more of a developmental way-station towards recognizing problems and devising patterns for governance architectures and socio-economic systems which describe generic and generative solutions to problems at scale that occur over and over again. Such patterns will help people understanding that commoning has no limits. Unless we set them. \n"
