        "text": "**For the sake of clarity**: our focus is not on \"scaling from below\". Spreading and applying the patterns of commoning to [Emulate & Federate] is certainly important, and it enacts what we call [[intercommoning]]. Nonetheless, it's more of a developmental way-station towards identifying problems and devising patterns for governance architectures and socio-economic systems which describe [http://coevolving.com/blogs/index.php/archive/systems-generating-systems-architectural-design-theory-by-christopher-alexander-1968/ generative solutions] to \"wicked\" problems in complex, transpersonal settings that occur over and over again. Such patterns will help people understanding that commoning has no limits. Unless we set them. \n"
